1
00:00:01,033 --> 00:00:02,700
<i>Attorney, do I still have
a fighting chance?</i>

2
00:00:05,067 --> 00:00:07,267
<i>Sorry, dear.
Papa can't come home.</i>

3
00:00:07,267 --> 00:00:08,467
<i> This is my fault.</i>

4
00:00:08,467 --> 00:00:11,767
<i>Whatever happened in the past
doesn't matter now.</i>

5
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:15,167
<i>All I want is for us
to be together again.</i>

6
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:17,433
<i>Do you really think Ryan
could smile like that</i>

7
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:18,733
<i> if he actually killed Anton?</i>

8
00:00:18,733 --> 00:00:20,100
<i> Who are you trying to fool?</i>

9
00:00:20,100 --> 00:00:21,300
<i> You just made that video</i>

10
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:23,100
<i>so you'd have an alibi
for the crime.</i>

11
00:00:23,100 --> 00:00:25,067
<i>That's exactly what
the prosecutor will tell me</i>

12
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,667
<i>once I present
that forwarded video.</i>

13
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:28,500
<i> You killed my son!</i>

14
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:31,433
<i>If you had held him
accountable for his actions,</i>

15
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:33,100
<i> we wouldn't be here!</i>

16
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,500
<i> You and your friends?</i>

17
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:36,300
<i> You all deserve to die!</i>

18
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:39,367
<i>Earlier, Ryan asked me
if we really had a chance.</i>

19
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:42,200
<i>I couldn't promise him
I could help.</i>

20
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,633
<i> Maybe Edong's right.</i>

21
00:00:43,633 --> 00:00:46,033
Maybe I can't save any of them.

22
00:00:46,033 --> 00:00:47,533
<i>That doesn't define
who you are.</i>

23
00:00:47,533 --> 00:00:49,533
<i>There's still something
I need to collect.</i>

24
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:52,467
<i>I have to fulfill the promises
I made to Attorney.</i>

25
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:56,967
[LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

26
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:11,233
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

27
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:28,267
Sweetheart, look.

28
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:31,733
This is what everyone's
talking about now.

29
00:02:32,767 --> 00:02:36,533
Anton Montenegro's death
here in Amurao.

30
00:02:37,533 --> 00:02:39,233
[CHUCKLES]

31
00:02:39,233 --> 00:02:40,667
All eyes are on this.

32
00:02:41,367 --> 00:02:43,400
[CHUCKLES]

33
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,833
In a few days,

34
00:02:45,533 --> 00:02:47,767
they'll forget about
that woman.

35
00:02:49,933 --> 00:02:52,267
That bastard Edong!

36
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:54,600
He buried that woman
near Ella's grave.

37
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,800
He took what was mine!

38
00:02:57,767 --> 00:03:04,733
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:03:18,767 --> 00:03:25,733
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

40
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,633
I told you about Ella,
didn't I?

41
00:03:39,633 --> 00:03:40,767
[SCOFFS] Fine...

42
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,333
...I'll tell you again.

43
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:47,333
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

44
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:51,133
Ella was my first.

45
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:54,833
Not my favorite.

46
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,300
But my first.

47
00:04:00,733 --> 00:04:03,300
Out of all the kids back then,

48
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,933
Ella had the most
beautiful smile.

49
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:10,333
<i> Help!</i>

50
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:17,300
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:04:24,700 --> 00:04:26,367
[ELLA CRYING] Mama!

52
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:27,833
<i> Papa!</i>

53
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,033
[KNOCKS]

54
00:04:32,033 --> 00:04:35,833
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

55
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:37,667
- [KNOCKS]
- [MEL] Alice.

56
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:40,567
Beth needs to talk to us.

57
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,300
Why?

58
00:04:43,267 --> 00:04:45,000
Is it about Ryan's case?

59
00:04:48,267 --> 00:04:50,700
- [BETH] Are we ready?
- [TIM] What about the others?

60
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,900
Oh my God, Tim!

61
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:55,333
- They're here.
- Wow!

62
00:04:55,333 --> 00:04:57,000
- Aw.
- Mel!

63
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:00,333
- I missed you.
- You're here.

64
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:01,667
Of course we are.

65
00:05:02,467 --> 00:05:05,633
When Erica and Beth called us
to ask if we could help,

66
00:05:05,633 --> 00:05:06,867
of course we said yes.

67
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:10,267
And obviously, us girls,

68
00:05:10,267 --> 00:05:12,033
we stick together.

69
00:05:12,033 --> 00:05:13,800
Don't worry.

70
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:16,567
We've got you, bitches!

71
00:05:16,567 --> 00:05:18,300
[GIGGLES] You're unbelievable.

72
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:19,867
[GIGGLING]

73
00:05:19,867 --> 00:05:22,600
[PHONE RINGING]

74
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,833
Go.

75
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:26,367
Yes, MJ?

76
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:27,533
Okay, confirmed.

77
00:05:28,267 --> 00:05:30,867
Casa Rosas Hotel, Leonora Hall.

78
00:05:31,867 --> 00:05:33,500
Okay. Thank you.

79
00:05:39,733 --> 00:05:41,567
When Tim said,

80
00:05:41,567 --> 00:05:44,100
"Beth and Erica called us..."

81
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:48,067
I never thought
I'd hear your names

82
00:05:48,067 --> 00:05:49,967
in the same sentence like that.

83
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:52,033
Yeah, actually.

84
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,200
[KNOCKS]

85
00:05:59,767 --> 00:06:06,733
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

86
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:11,000
<i> Uh...</i>

87
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,633
<i>Do you want to go over
my counter-evidence</i>

88
00:06:13,633 --> 00:06:14,733
<i> for tomorrow's inquest?</i>

89
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:16,933
<i> Is that why you called?</i>

90
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,133
<i> Let's do it.</i>

91
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,167
<i> I agree.</i>

92
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:25,733
<i> Come in.</i>

93
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:37,867
<i> Erica, what you said before...</i>

94
00:06:37,867 --> 00:06:41,933
<i>Let's just tell everyone
the truth about Edong.</i>

95
00:06:48,567 --> 00:06:50,967
<i>I don't think that'll change
anything, Beth.</i>

96
00:06:52,967 --> 00:06:55,933
<i>Edong's been consumed
by anger and revenge.</i>

97
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:59,967
<i>Even if we tell the truth,
he won't stop.</i>

98
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:03,933
<i>What happened
to Anton proves that.</i>

99
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,033
<i> So does what happened to Ryan.</i>

100
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:09,700
<i> Marco's right.</i>

101
00:07:11,133 --> 00:07:15,133
<i>We have to find him
and stop him.</i>

102
00:07:17,867 --> 00:07:20,067
<i>Erica, I'm not doing this
for Edong.</i>

103
00:07:22,033 --> 00:07:25,133
<i>I'm doing this for me
and my family.</i>

104
00:07:27,567 --> 00:07:32,133
<i>Chloe said earlier
she wants a reset for us.</i>

105
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:38,133
<i> To go back to being happy.</i>

106
00:07:39,067 --> 00:07:40,800
<i> To being together.</i>

107
00:07:43,267 --> 00:07:44,800
<i> I realized...</i>

108
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:48,700
<i>I'm the one who can
press that button.</i>

109
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:50,000
<i> For us.</i>

110
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,000
<i> That lie I told...</i>

111
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:57,000
<i>I've been carrying it
for years.</i>

112
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:00,833
<i>It's like a curse
that won't let me go.</i>

113
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:06,000
<i>Maybe if I finally admit
the truth about Edong,</i>

114
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,733
<i> I can start over.</i>

115
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,933
<i>I won't have to pretend
anymore.</i>

116
00:08:13,633 --> 00:08:15,933
<i>I won't have to feel
ashamed in front of my child.</i>

117
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:18,733
<i> And maybe...</i>

118
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,767
<i> ...I can forgive myself.</i>

119
00:08:25,900 --> 00:08:28,900
<i>Because of that selfish
decision I made.</i>

120
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:31,700
<i> The one that ruined me.</i>

121
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:35,967
<i>The one that keeps hurting
the people I love.</i>

122
00:08:37,967 --> 00:08:42,667
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

123
00:08:42,667 --> 00:08:43,900
<i> Erica, please.</i>

124
00:08:44,633 --> 00:08:46,000
<i> Help me.</i>

125
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,800
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

126
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:50,967
<i> Are you sure?</i>

127
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:53,800
<i> Yes. I'm sure.</i>

128
00:08:54,833 --> 00:08:59,133
Hey, it's okay if you guys
sit this one out.

129
00:08:59,967 --> 00:09:03,200
We know you're going
through things too.

130
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,967
Erica and I can handle this.

131
00:09:04,967 --> 00:09:07,200
- I'm in.
- Yeah, me too.

132
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,600
F**k it.
I have nothing left to lose.

133
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:13,900
We're just waiting
for Erica and Ryan.

134
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:20,367
If the prosecutor can't find
solid evidence against Ryan,

135
00:09:20,367 --> 00:09:22,233
he can walk free today, right?

136
00:09:25,267 --> 00:09:28,900
Ryan and I agreed
I won't attend the inquest.

137
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:32,000
I'll focus on this instead.

138
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:36,800
I might lose it and argue
with the prosecutor.

139
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,133
[CHUCKLES]

140
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:43,133
And we also agreed
that no matter what happens,

141
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:44,933
we go through with this.

142
00:09:50,967 --> 00:09:57,933
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

143
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:01,100
[CHUCKLING]

144
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:02,967
Prosecutor.

145
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:05,133
Go ahead, Attorney.

146
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:08,033
I'm fully aware that
good moral character

147
00:10:08,033 --> 00:10:09,900
is not proof of innocence.

148
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,667
Reputation alone
cannot acquit a man.

149
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:14,200
Still, I submit
this certificate

150
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,133
reflecting the life
my client has lived.

151
00:10:17,167 --> 00:10:19,367
No trouble.
No enemies.

152
00:10:19,933 --> 00:10:22,067
Clean records
in the<i> barangay</i> and police

153
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:24,067
until the crime happened.

154
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,833
I'm not talking about
Anton Montenegro's murder.

155
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,400
I'm talking about
Ryan Mora being framed.

156
00:10:30,233 --> 00:10:33,867
Atty. Melendez,
I'm fully aware

157
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:38,700
this is irrelevant
to Mr. Mora's case.

158
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,467
I've encountered men
like that before.

159
00:10:41,467 --> 00:10:46,500
Long regarded as having
good moral character.

160
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:48,267
Men of faith.

161
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:52,167
Loved and worshipped
by their kingdom.

162
00:10:52,767 --> 00:10:53,900
No trouble.

163
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:56,767
No enemies except Satan.

164
00:10:57,967 --> 00:11:00,933
Clean records as well.

165
00:11:00,933 --> 00:11:05,033
Until girls as young as twelve
went to the police

166
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:10,367
and spoke about
the sexual abuse

167
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,233
he committed against them.

168
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:17,967
Attorney, that argument
collapses anywhere.

169
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:23,300
Yes, this certificate
looks impressive.

170
00:11:23,967 --> 00:11:27,067
But in my office,
it's just paper.

171
00:11:27,067 --> 00:11:32,033
Papers that are easily burned
when the truth is lit.

172
00:11:32,467 --> 00:11:34,067
And this fainting incident?

173
00:11:34,067 --> 00:11:35,400
- Self-serving.
- Prosecutor--

174
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:38,433
No medicolegal justification.

175
00:11:38,433 --> 00:11:42,567
I'm not wasting my time
arguing about something

176
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,767
that technically
did not happen.

177
00:11:47,867 --> 00:11:52,967
Edong Santiago called you
and confessed to everything.

178
00:11:53,433 --> 00:11:57,300
So now you're claiming
this is all a frame-up.

179
00:11:57,967 --> 00:11:59,500
Yes, Prosecutor.

180
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,300
The call logs show

181
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,500
the number that called us
is the same number

182
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:05,933
that gave the anonymous tip
to the police.

183
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:07,933
And you know our history
with Edong.

184
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:09,233
He clearly has a motive.

185
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:12,800
I've read that already,
Attorney.

186
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,300
I don't need your lecture.

187
00:12:15,333 --> 00:12:18,967
I know your history
with Santiago.

188
00:12:19,567 --> 00:12:23,233
You've caused
more than enough trouble here.

189
00:12:23,233 --> 00:12:25,533
The whole of Amurao
has been dragged into this.

190
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:29,600
Let's be clear.

191
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:34,467
Your claim that Edong
called and confessed

192
00:12:34,467 --> 00:12:36,300
is self-serving.

193
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:38,500
There's no independent proof.

194
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:41,933
No recording.
No witness.

195
00:12:42,467 --> 00:12:47,367
And a phone call proves nothing
about the murder of the victim.

196
00:12:50,067 --> 00:12:52,267
But, Prosecutor,
the matching numbers--

197
00:12:52,267 --> 00:12:55,267
The call logs only prove
that someone called you.

198
00:12:55,267 --> 00:12:59,067
Even if Santiago
hates you so much,

199
00:12:59,067 --> 00:13:02,167
that doesn't automatically mean
he killed Mr. Montenegro.

200
00:13:02,167 --> 00:13:08,300
And it certainly doesn't prove
that Mr. Mora didn't.

201
00:13:09,567 --> 00:13:11,400
Sir, I'm not asking you
to treat it

202
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,433
as a full confession.

203
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:15,567
I'm asking you to see it
as part of a pattern.

204
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:19,333
A man with a motive
calls to threaten our lives

205
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:22,400
using the same number
that tipped off the police

206
00:13:22,433 --> 00:13:24,267
to the crime scene.

207
00:13:24,267 --> 00:13:26,200
Where the evidence is too neat.

208
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,533
Too perfect.

209
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:29,200
This isn't just drama.

210
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,600
This is orchestration.

211
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:34,467
As of the moment,
the only clear data I have is

212
00:13:34,467 --> 00:13:40,333
that Anton Montenegro's corpse
was found at Mr. Mora's shop.

213
00:13:41,133 --> 00:13:46,167
The murder weapon next to him
was held by your client.

214
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:50,367
They only saw
the victim's blood

215
00:13:50,367 --> 00:13:52,233
and Mr. Mora's fingerprints.

216
00:13:53,033 --> 00:13:55,400
There was no trace
of Santiago.

217
00:13:56,133 --> 00:13:57,333
[DONATO SNICKERS]

218
00:13:57,333 --> 00:14:02,400
Attorney, isn't this enough
to proceed with the case?

219
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:05,467
Is that what we should be
asking right now, Prosecutor?

220
00:14:05,467 --> 00:14:07,000
Shouldn't we instead be asking

221
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,467
if there's a realistic
chance of conviction?

222
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:10,433
Or are we simply sending
somebody to trial

223
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:12,967
because he's the most
convenient body at the scene?

224
00:14:14,567 --> 00:14:16,067
Atty. Melendez,

225
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:18,467
are you trying
to ask questions,

226
00:14:18,467 --> 00:14:20,667
or are you trying
to school me,

227
00:14:20,667 --> 00:14:22,267
just like what you do
when you show off

228
00:14:22,267 --> 00:14:23,967
at your Congressional hearings?

229
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:27,233
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

230
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:29,300
[DONATO] Is that the video
you're telling me about?

231
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:35,967
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

232
00:14:38,633 --> 00:14:39,967
[RYAN ON VIDEO]
<i> What's that, dude?</i>

233
00:14:39,967 --> 00:14:41,367
<i> Evidence for your girlfriend?</i>

234
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:43,367
<i> Oh, dear. Don't--</i>

235
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:45,033
- [MAN 1 ON VIDEO]<i> Hey there!
</i>- [MAN 2 ON VIDEO] Sir!

236
00:14:45,033 --> 00:14:46,100
[RYAN ON VIDEO] Yes?

237
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:53,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

238
00:14:53,433 --> 00:14:57,633
Is this the video you're hoping
will change everything?

239
00:14:57,633 --> 00:14:59,167
Sir, if you can watch
the whole clip--

240
00:14:59,167 --> 00:15:00,733
[DONATO] The whole clip?

241
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:04,500
Right now, we only have
a video that is vertical,

242
00:15:04,500 --> 00:15:09,600
shaky, corrupted, easy to edit,
and easy to forward.

243
00:15:10,067 --> 00:15:12,233
And I am yet to receive
a medicolegal report stating

244
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:16,500
that Mr. Mora's timeline
makes it impossible for him

245
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:17,967
to have committed the crime.

246
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:21,300
Without that,
that video...

247
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,700
is just noise.

248
00:15:23,700 --> 00:15:26,100
Then let's focus on
what we do have, Prosecutor.

249
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,667
The crime scene report shows

250
00:15:27,667 --> 00:15:29,200
that there wasn't enough blood
at the shop

251
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,333
- to match the severity--
- Atty. Melendez,

252
00:15:31,333 --> 00:15:33,267
you're not a forensic expert.

253
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:35,800
Scene notes are not conclusive.

254
00:15:35,833 --> 00:15:37,733
Without a medicolegal report,

255
00:15:37,733 --> 00:15:41,700
your theory is nothing
but mere speculation.

256
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:44,700
You're trying to
outrun a report

257
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:47,333
that has not even
formally arrived.

258
00:15:47,333 --> 00:15:49,767
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:15:49,767 --> 00:15:51,333
I have no choice,

260
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:53,533
but to file a case
against Mr. Mora.

261
00:15:56,667 --> 00:15:57,633
Sir.

262
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,200
Mr. Relucio.

263
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,333
[DONATO] Lieutenant Colonel.

264
00:16:03,333 --> 00:16:07,300
I have with me the preliminary
medicolegal report.

265
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,500
Here's your copy, sir.

266
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:12,433
Attorney.

267
00:16:12,433 --> 00:16:19,333
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

268
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,267
Uh, Prosecutor, if I may...

269
00:16:35,267 --> 00:16:36,500
Go ahead, Attorney.

270
00:16:37,267 --> 00:16:39,233
Prosecutor, the report
is clearly leaning

271
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:40,600
toward a secondary scene.

272
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,233
The killing didn't happen
at Mr. Mora's shop.

273
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:47,767
This is a preliminary finding,
Atty. Melendez.

274
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:50,400
The TOD estimate
and those patterns

275
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:52,533
can still change
in the final one.

276
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:56,300
The report says that
Mr. Montenegro likely died

277
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:57,700
at 2:30 in the morning.

278
00:16:58,167 --> 00:16:59,567
We know from
the sworn statements

279
00:16:59,567 --> 00:17:01,233
of Edgar Mata and Art Lacuña

280
00:17:01,233 --> 00:17:04,600
that there was a video sent
at 3:17 in the morning

281
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:08,133
of Ryan lucid, supervising
the work at the shop.

282
00:17:08,133 --> 00:17:10,567
That's 47 minutes
after the estimated killing.

283
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:13,333
The video shows,
once we see the full clip,

284
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:16,433
that it's not just a cute video
for Edgar's girlfriend.

285
00:17:16,467 --> 00:17:18,933
It's an objective alibi
that your TOD anchors.

286
00:17:18,933 --> 00:17:20,833
It's still an estimate,
Attorney.

287
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:24,600
TOD windows have
margins of error.

288
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,333
And we haven't even seen

289
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:28,933
the full clip
you're talking about.

290
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:30,267
[DONATO SNICKERS]

291
00:17:30,267 --> 00:17:31,633
Some magic could
still have happened

292
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:34,833
in the 47 minutes
you've mentioned.

293
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,267
Yes, Prosecutor.

294
00:17:36,267 --> 00:17:38,300
That's a valid trial theory

295
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:40,133
if the forensics supported
the cleanup

296
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:42,200
and restaging within the shop.

297
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,467
However, that's not
what your report is saying.

298
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:46,133
No high-velocity spatter

299
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:48,700
on the walls, the ceiling,
or the tools.

300
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:50,633
No cast-off patterns.

301
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:53,667
And blood pooling suggests
prior pooling and transfer.

302
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:57,133
Foreign fibers that don't even
belong in this environment.

303
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:58,467
The report is telling you

304
00:17:58,467 --> 00:18:00,867
that the shop is not where
he was beaten to death.

305
00:18:01,367 --> 00:18:03,833
The shop is where
his body was delivered.

306
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:10,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

307
00:18:10,633 --> 00:18:11,633
[DONATO] Okay.

308
00:18:11,633 --> 00:18:13,467
For the sake of argument,

309
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:15,700
let's assume that the shop
is a secondary scene.

310
00:18:16,233 --> 00:18:18,467
He could still have helped
bring the body,

311
00:18:18,467 --> 00:18:19,900
stage the scene,

312
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:22,200
and hit the victim
somewhere else.

313
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:25,733
I appreciate the argument,
Attorney.

314
00:18:26,233 --> 00:18:28,400
But I still don't have
a document in front of me

315
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:33,300
stating that Mr. Mora's
participation was impossible.

316
00:18:36,933 --> 00:18:41,767
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

317
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:43,833
Come on, let's do this.

318
00:18:43,833 --> 00:18:44,767
Well?

319
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:46,000
Still no update?

320
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,367
We're about to start.

321
00:18:48,367 --> 00:18:50,000
Still no update.

322
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,900
Not even a text from Erica.

323
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:56,567
Shoot! What if...

324
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,700
What if they proceeded
to file a case against Ryan?

325
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,733
What if he failed
to answer properly?

326
00:19:01,433 --> 00:19:03,767
Sometimes, he panics easily.

327
00:19:03,767 --> 00:19:05,733
That's why I always
accompany him.

328
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:10,367
Maybe I should go to him.
What do you think?

329
00:19:10,967 --> 00:19:12,233
[RYAN] Love!

330
00:19:13,533 --> 00:19:14,767
[BETH] Love!

331
00:19:14,767 --> 00:19:16,900
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

332
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:25,367
[TENDER MUSIC PLAYING]

333
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:35,933
<i>- Sir, excuse me.
- [MARCO PANTS]</i>

334
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:37,933
Uh, Prosecutor, Attorney Erica,

335
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:40,733
<i>I'm sorry,
but you need to see this.</i>

336
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:44,867
<i> Hold this.</i>

337
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:50,633
<i>Sir, this is the phone of one
of Mr. Mora's mechanics,</i>

338
00:19:50,633 --> 00:19:51,633
<i> Edgar Mata.</i>

339
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:53,067
<i> It got damaged,</i>

340
00:19:53,067 --> 00:19:54,467
<i>but it's now working
after being repaired.</i>

341
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,800
<i>Prosecutor, we'd like
to present to you</i>

342
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:58,667
<i>the original source
of the video</i>

343
00:19:58,667 --> 00:20:00,767
<i>sent to Edgar Mata's
girlfriend.</i>

344
00:20:00,767 --> 00:20:03,733
<i>This contains the full video
with the original metadata.</i>

345
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:05,667
<i> Okay. Play it.</i>

346
00:20:05,667 --> 00:20:07,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

347
00:20:07,867 --> 00:20:09,800
[EDGAR ON VIDEO] Do you want me
to introduce you

348
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,300
<i> to my side chick, love?</i>

349
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:12,667
<i> My goodness.</i>

350
00:20:12,667 --> 00:20:14,600
<i>We've been together
all night long.</i>

351
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:15,767
<i> We're right here.</i>

352
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:16,833
<i> See?</i>

353
00:20:17,767 --> 00:20:19,700
<i> What's that, dude?</i>

354
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:21,367
<i> Evidence for your girlfriend?</i>

355
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:23,367
<i> Oh, dear. Don't--</i>

356
00:20:23,367 --> 00:20:24,800
- [MAN 1 ON VIDEO]<i> Hey there!
</i>- [MAN 2 ON VIDEO] Sir!

357
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:25,767
[RYAN ON VIDEO] Yes?

358
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:29,833
<i> Do you believe me now?</i>

359
00:20:31,967 --> 00:20:36,800
"Saturday - November 9, 2024
- 3:15 AM"

360
00:20:37,567 --> 00:20:42,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

361
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:47,033
<i>Prosecutor, your own evidence
shows Mr. Mora working,</i>

362
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:48,367
<i> relaxed,</i>

363
00:20:48,367 --> 00:20:49,733
<i> even joking with his workers</i>

364
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:52,533
<i>45 minutes
after the estimated killing.</i>

365
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:55,567
<i>And somewhere out there,
we have a man with a motive,</i>

366
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:58,433
<i>who called us to announce
what he was going to do</i>

367
00:20:58,633 --> 00:21:00,900
<i>using the same number
to send the anonymous tip</i>

368
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:03,433
<i>to the officers that led them
straight to this setup.</i>

369
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:06,800
<i>You could say that
the mechanics are lying...</i>

370
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,400
<i> that the video is fake.</i>

371
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,033
<i> You can even say that...</i>

372
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:12,333
<i>the time of death is
only an approximation.</i>

373
00:21:12,733 --> 00:21:14,667
<i>But you have to answer this,
Prosecutor.</i>

374
00:21:15,033 --> 00:21:18,367
<i>If this were a conspiracy
to create a fake alibi,</i>

375
00:21:18,367 --> 00:21:19,933
<i>why would they risk
killing Mr. Montenegro</i>

376
00:21:19,933 --> 00:21:21,067
<i> somewhere else?</i>

377
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:22,933
<i> Having to move a body,</i>

378
00:21:22,933 --> 00:21:24,567
<i> stage a crime scene,</i>

379
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:26,100
<i> hoping that the timing,</i>

380
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:30,700
<i>the blood, the fibers,
the TOD, and the video</i>

381
00:21:30,700 --> 00:21:33,567
<i>would all perfectly line up
in their favor.</i>

382
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:36,067
<i>It would have been easier
to kill him at the shop</i>

383
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:38,900
<i>and let everything
look natural.</i>

384
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:41,433
<i> But that's not what happened.</i>

385
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:44,100
<i>Right now, the only thing
tying Mr. Mora to this case</i>

386
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:45,800
<i>is his physical presence
in the room</i>

387
00:21:45,800 --> 00:21:48,700
<i>that your own forensics
are screaming is staged.</i>

388
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:51,100
<i>But where was Mr. Montenegro
in the video?</i>

389
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,767
<i> There was no corpse around.</i>

390
00:21:53,633 --> 00:21:55,700
<i> Not even a bloodstain.</i>

391
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:58,700
<i>The accused has
no wounds or scratches.</i>

392
00:21:58,967 --> 00:22:00,567
<i> There's no magic.</i>

393
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:02,733
<i> So, the question is not</i>

394
00:22:02,733 --> 00:22:05,433
<i>about whether we can
technically file this case.</i>

395
00:22:05,433 --> 00:22:07,967
<i>The question is about
whether you honestly believe</i>

396
00:22:07,967 --> 00:22:11,400
that there's a realistic chance
<i> of convicting him</i>

397
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,933
<i>without lying to yourself
about your own evidence.</i>

398
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,967
<i>And if we still insist
pinning this crime on him,</i>

399
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,000
<i>despite the fact that's
been staring us in the face,</i>

400
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:22,800
<i>then let's call it
by its real name.</i>

401
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:25,433
<i> Injustice.</i>

402
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:33,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

403
00:22:54,433 --> 00:22:56,400
So, does this mean
you're in the clear now?

404
00:22:56,933 --> 00:22:59,700
Well, love, it was amazing.

405
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:00,767
I felt like we were in a movie.

406
00:23:00,767 --> 00:23:01,867
At the very last minute,

407
00:23:01,867 --> 00:23:03,800
the preliminary medicolegal
report finally came,

408
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,867
stating that Anton had
been dead for two hours

409
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:07,067
when he was found at the shop.

410
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:10,133
But the prosecutor still
deemed it insufficient.

411
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:12,533
Luckily, Marco arrived.

412
00:23:12,533 --> 00:23:14,667
He brought
our strongest evidence.

413
00:23:15,033 --> 00:23:18,100
Well, she said the video
wouldn't be useful

414
00:23:18,100 --> 00:23:20,100
if it wasn't from
the original source.

415
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:22,400
So, I had the phone of
Ryan's mechanic fixed.

416
00:23:22,733 --> 00:23:28,500
The video proved that
they were working together.

417
00:23:28,500 --> 00:23:30,867
Ryan was totally fine
and didn't have any wounds

418
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:34,067
a few minutes after Anton's
estimated time of death.

419
00:23:34,067 --> 00:23:36,233
Oh, thank you so much.

420
00:23:36,233 --> 00:23:38,200
Erica, thank you so much.

421
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:39,700
I owe you a lot.

422
00:23:42,133 --> 00:23:45,567
- [GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

423
00:23:45,567 --> 00:23:47,533
I kept this along with...

424
00:23:48,133 --> 00:23:50,800
everything related
to our high school life.

425
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:55,100
I said I wanted to move on.

426
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:57,967
But the truth is...

427
00:24:00,267 --> 00:24:01,600
I wanted to forget it

428
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:02,933
because I felt embarrassed,

429
00:24:02,933 --> 00:24:04,900
and my conscience
was eating me up.

430
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,767
But now, I'm wearing it.

431
00:24:08,767 --> 00:24:09,900
Is that okay?

432
00:24:12,167 --> 00:24:18,267
[SOFT INSTRUMENTAL
OF "SABAY-SABAY TAYO"]

433
00:24:18,267 --> 00:24:20,667
- W-Why not?
- [CHUCKLES]

434
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:22,700
Of course, it's okay!

435
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:23,900
[MEL] Well, what do you expect?

436
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,867
That I'm going to tell you
to take that off

437
00:24:25,867 --> 00:24:26,867
because I don't want you
as my friend?

438
00:24:26,867 --> 00:24:28,000
Of course not!

439
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,767
You're the only ones
I have left.

440
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,067
[CHUCKLING]

441
00:24:31,067 --> 00:24:31,933
[MEL] I'm serious.

442
00:24:32,633 --> 00:24:34,700
I'm glad that I have you.

443
00:24:35,700 --> 00:24:42,700
[SOFT INSTRUMENTAL OF
"SABAY-SABAY TAYO" CONTINUES]

444
00:24:42,700 --> 00:24:45,267
<i> Yay! We have matching
bracelets!</i> [CHUCKLES]

445
00:24:45,267 --> 00:24:47,000
<i> You're so corny!</i>

446
00:24:50,267 --> 00:24:51,267
Go.

447
00:24:51,267 --> 00:24:52,600
[CLEARS THROAT]

448
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:54,067
Sorry, I know you're having
a special moment here,

449
00:24:54,067 --> 00:24:55,767
but it's game time.

450
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:06,533
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]
- [CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING]

451
00:25:06,567 --> 00:25:08,567
We asked you all
to come here today

452
00:25:09,767 --> 00:25:11,733
to give a statement

453
00:25:11,733 --> 00:25:13,733
about the death
of Anton Montenegro

454
00:25:15,167 --> 00:25:17,333
and an incident that
happened 14 years ago.

455
00:25:17,333 --> 00:25:24,233
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

456
00:25:46,267 --> 00:25:47,967
<i>- Oh, Auntie!
- Over there.</i>

457
00:25:47,967 --> 00:25:51,133
<i> Lying has consequences.</i>

458
00:25:51,133 --> 00:25:53,867
<i> Don't you understand that?</i>

459
00:25:53,867 --> 00:25:55,367
<i> It's not yet too late, Edong.</i>

460
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:56,533
<i> We are changing the story.</i>

461
00:25:56,533 --> 00:25:58,367
<i>We are trying
to make things right.</i>

462
00:25:58,367 --> 00:26:00,300
<i> Liars!</i>

463
00:26:00,300 --> 00:26:02,333
<i> I'll make you pay!</i>

464
00:26:02,333 --> 00:26:06,667
<i>It's so satisfying to
watch you fall apart.</i>

465
00:26:06,667 --> 00:26:09,333
<i> You should die.</i>

466
00:26:09,367 --> 00:26:11,733
<i> My dear!</i> [WAILING]

467
00:26:11,733 --> 00:26:14,133
<i>I knew you'd need something
from me, Attorney.</i>

468
00:26:14,133 --> 00:26:15,967
<i> We need him to lure Edong out.</i>

469
00:26:15,967 --> 00:26:17,667
<i> Erica, he killed my mother!</i>

470
00:26:17,667 --> 00:26:20,300
<i>Edong will kill even more
if we don't do this!</i>

471
00:26:20,300 --> 00:26:23,367
<i>So, if you want to save what's
left of your brother's soul,</i>

472
00:26:23,367 --> 00:26:24,667
<i> we need to do this!</i>

473
00:26:24,667 --> 00:26:25,833
<i> I knew it.</i>

474
00:26:25,833 --> 00:26:27,200
<i> You'd turn out just like me.</i>

475
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:28,900
<i> No!</i>

476
00:26:28,900 --> 00:26:29,967
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [GRUNTS]
